                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1148">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.512/219: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-30T22:00:00+02:00"
                            >January 30, 1943—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 31—8:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>196. Department’s 94, January 29, 5 p.m. I perceive no objection to the
                    Department recommending to the Department of Commerce the issuance of a
                    statement to American exporters to the effect that the Turkish Government is
                    prepared to guarantee payment to American exporters for exports to Turkey which
                    Turkish merchants are unable to pay for on account of the capital tax.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
